3 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
4 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6060.52 of Title 36, unless
5 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
6 A. An enrollee may choose to pay out of pocket for a health
7 care service from a health care provider. If an enrollee obtains a
8 medically necessary health care service covered by his or her health
9 benefit plan and negotiates for a price lower than the average
10 allowed amount established by the benefit plan and provided to the
11 enrollee upon request, and the enrollee pays out of pocket for the
12 health care service, the enrollee may electronically send
13 documentation to the carrier that provides the following:
14 1. The health care service the enrollee or patient received and
15 the name of the health care provider and contact information;
16 2. If an order by the health care provider is required by the
17 policy, the order from the health care provider given to the
18 enrollee or patient and the final bill or statement for the health
19 care service; and
20 3. The negotiated cost of the health care service that the
21 enrollee received and that:
22 a. the enrollee paid out of pocket for the health care
23 services received, and
24
SB515 HFLR Page 4
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 b. the health care entity is not making a claim against
2 the carrier for payment for the health care service
3 provided to the enrollee or patient.
4 B. The health care provider shall accept the payment from the
5 enrollee as payment in full and shall not bill the enrollee or the
6 health benefit plan for any balance between the amount collected
7 from the enrollee and the billed charge for the service by the
8 provider.
9 C. A carrier that receives the documentation described in
10 subsection A of this section shall count the full amount that the
11 enrollee paid out of pocket toward the deductible and annual maximum
12 out-of-pocket expense if:
13 1. The health care service is covered under the health benefit
14 plan of the enrollee; and
15 2. The enrollee negotiated for a lower cost for the health care
16 service than the average allowed amount established by his or her
17 health benefit plan for that covered health care service.
18 D. The amount of the out-of-pocket cost shall be attributed to
19 the in-network deductible and annual maximum out-of-pocket expense
20 if the provider was an in-network provider, and to the out-of-
21 network deductible and annual maximum out-of-pocket expense if the
22 provider was an out-of-network provider.
23 E. The amount counted toward an applicable out-of-pocket
24 deductible and annual maximum out-of-pocket expense shall not exceed
SB515 HFLR Page 5
